question.text:
A system has n resources R0, R1, …, Rn - 1, and k 
processes P0, P1, …, Pk - 1 . The implementation of 
the resource request logic of each process Pi,  is as 
follows: 

if (i% 2 == 0) { 

if (i < n) request Ri;  

if (i + 2 < n) request Ri + 2;   

} 

else { 

if (i < n) request Rn - i; 

if (i + 2 < n) request Rn - i- 2 ; 

} 

In which one of the following situations is a deadlock 
possible?
